{"title":"CeramicSpeed Drops New $669 OSPW X for SRAM RED XPLR AXS","link":"https://bikerumor.com/ceramicspeed-drops-new-669-ospw-x-for-sram-red-xplr-axs/","date":1740066924000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-full--1406x2500.webp\" width=\"1406\" height=\"2500\" alt=\"\" /></p>\n<p>For the big pulley believers out there, CeramicSpeed is bringing its OSPW X system to the SRAM RED XPLR AXS groupset. The new OSPW X isn’t just about oversized pulleys (though it is a lot of it). It’s about tackling the unique demands of gravel riding with “next-level engineering.”</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-08-scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1407\" height=\"2500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-08-1407x2500.webp\" alt=\"Chain and wheels \" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-08-1407x2500.webp 1407w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-08-169x300.webp 169w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-08-68x120.webp 68w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-08-768x1365.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-08-864x1536.webp 864w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-08-1152x2048.webp 1152w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-08-scaled.webp 1440w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-full--scaled-e1739900098894.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1406\" height=\"2500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-full--1406x2500.webp\" alt=\"pully wheels \" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/ceramicspeed-ospw-x-eagle-expands-fast-derailleur-upgrades-further-off-road/\">OSPW X </a>was first introduced with SRAM Eagle Transmission. The unique ( and, dare I say, stylish) design boasts some practical features and efficiency: Active Debris Remover (ADR) and ALPHA Disc pulleys.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-close-up-.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1102\" height=\"736\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-close-up-.png\" alt=\"close up on wheels \" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-close-up-.png 1102w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-close-up--297x198.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-close-up--120x80.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-close-up--768x513.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-close-up--800x533.png 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-close-up--720x480.png 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Gravel – Active Debris Remover (ADR)</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Debris is the enemy of smooth shifting, especially on rough gravel roads. That’s where ADR steps in. This patent-pending system uses a unique dust cover anchored securely in a groove on the pulley wheel, fully sealing off the bearing. Surrounding that is a bladed groove structure designed to eject debris as the wheel spins. Keep sticks, stones, and anything else that will break your bones out of the pully wheel.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-pair-.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1410\" height=\"778\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-pair-.png\" alt=\"training in the snow \" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-pair-.png 1410w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-pair--297x164.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-pair--120x66.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-pair--768x424.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Translation?</em></strong> Your drivetrain stays cleaner and more efficient, with fewer hiding places for dirt and debris.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>CeramicSpeed didn’t just create this in the lab—it’s been rigorously tested with its pro-off-road teams, ensuring it can handle real-world abuse.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-big--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1406\" height=\"2500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-big--1406x2500.webp\" alt=\"Side view of the pully wheel set \" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-big--1406x2500.webp 1406w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-big--169x300.webp 169w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-big--67x120.webp 67w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-big--768x1366.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-big--864x1536.webp 864w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-big--1152x2048.webp 1152w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-big--scaled.webp 1440w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-17-scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1407\" height=\"2500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-17-1407x2500.webp\" alt=\"Chain line SRAM \" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-17-1407x2500.webp 1407w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-17-169x300.webp 169w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-17-68x120.webp 68w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-17-768x1365.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-17-864x1536.webp 864w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-17-1152x2048.webp 1152w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ceramic-speed-sponsorkomorebi-17-scaled.webp 1440w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>ALPHA Disc</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The OSPW X for RED XPLR AXS has 14-tooth and 20-tooth ALPHA Disc pulleys, which feature a two-piece design. The narrow-wide composite teeth enhance wear resistance and reduce noise, while the solid aluminum disc prevents debris from jamming the spokes.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-on-the-road--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-on-the-road--scaled.webp\" alt=\"NDS pulley wheel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-on-the-road--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-on-the-road--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-on-the-road--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-on-the-road--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-on-the-road--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-on-the-road--2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-on-the-road--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-on-the-road--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Built Tough, Built Light</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The OSPW X cage is crafted from reinforced molded carbon fiber, keeping weight low without compromising strength or durability. The whole system is dialed in for gravel riding, where reliability matters as much as performance.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new OSPW X for SRAM Red XPLR AXS has a reinforced molded carbon fiber cage to achieve strength, durability, and minimal weight.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-color-options-.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1926\" height=\"776\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-color-options-.png\" alt=\"Color options \" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-color-options-.png 1926w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-color-options--297x120.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-color-options--1536x619.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-color-options--120x48.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/CeramicSpeed-Drops-New-OSPW-X-for-SRAM-RED-XPLR-AXS-color-options--768x309.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As awesome as the OSPW X sounds, you can’t ignore the price. At $669, the cage and pulleys are just $31 shy of the price for the entire SRAM RED XPLR AXS rear derailleur. But if you’ve got cash to burn and marginal gains in your sights, it will make your derailleur stand out. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Pricing and Availability</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Price: </strong>$669</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Weight:</strong> N/A</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Colors: </strong>Silver or Black with Alpha finish</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Stay tuned for a full review, actual weights, and photos; we have one on the way.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://ceramicspeed.com/products/ospw-x-for-sram-red-xplr-e1\">www.ceramicspeed.com</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/ceramicspeed-drops-new-669-ospw-x-for-sram-red-xplr-axs/\">CeramicSpeed Drops New $669 OSPW X for SRAM RED XPLR AXS</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"91d30db50b7c1d84551374caffcd37754e8616b4e71929413fa1fa0eace74fb3","category":"Cycling"}